    "headline": "From Cisco to Block, more companies are pointing to AI when unveiling job cuts",
    "summary": "AI is rarely the sole reason companies cite when taking layoffs, with most still pointing to wider corporate restructuring or macroeconomic headwinds.  On Wednesday, Cisco Systems announced plans to cut under 4,000 jobs, or about 5% of its workforce.  The announcement arrived the same day the tech giant unveiled record revenue for its third fiscal quarter, amid soaring demand for its AI tools and infrastructure.",
